  28.5.45 ESMF_ArraySync - Synchronize DEs across the Array in case of sharing

   INTERFACE:
   subroutine ESMF_ArraySync(array, rc)

   ARGUMENTS:
     type(ESMF_Array), intent(in)            :: array
 -- The following arguments require argument keyword syntax (e.g. rc=rc). --
     integer,          intent(out), optional :: rc

   DESCRIPTION:

   Synchronizes access to DEs across array to make sure PETs correctly
   access the data for read and write when DEs are shared.

   The arguments are:

   array
          Specified ESMF_Array object.

   [rc]
          Return code; equals ESMF_SUCCESS if there are no errors.

